From CONF-15861,

A user has create permissions within a space, but cannot remove pages from it. They now get this text in the UI when moving a page:

{quote}You can not move this page to another space because you do not have permission to remove pages from this space.
You can move the highlighted page by dragging it to a new position in the tree.
{quote}

This first line is unhelpful and confusing. It should only show the second line, as before.

Stephen agrees with this. The fact that they do not have permission is implied by the fact that the UI does not give them the option to choose a space. This is analogous to a user who does not have edit permission on a page - they simply do not see the 'Edit' button - there is no text to explain why they cannot see it.

This bug is reported against the appropriate plugin at [http://developer.atlassian.com/jira/browse/SQL-58], but since it is caused by a change in Confluence we should keep it open here until we're sure that we aren't going to revert the Confluence change to solve it.

Use wiki markup such as:

{noformat}{sql:dataSource=CustomerDB}
SELECT region_name || ' ' || store_name FROM Geography
WHERE store_name = 'Boston';
{sql}

{sql}
count(*), x != 2 
{sql}

{noformat}



After switching to RTE andback this becomes:

{noformat}{sql:dataSource=CustomerDB}
SELECT region_name \|\| ' ' \|\| store_name FROM Geography
WHERE store_name = 'Boston';
{sql}

{sql}
count(*y) , x \!= 2
{sql}
{noformat}

Which is no longer a valid query.

This did not happen in 2.10.

